The Center for Sustainable Landscapes and Communities was created to conduct research and facilitate dialogue on the planning and management of public lands in Boulder and its surrounding areas.
Gifts to the CSLC will support the Center’s four main goals:
1) Engage the community: to engage all members of the community in active discourse, to better understand our relationships and needs with public lands;
2) Build knowledge: to investigate and analyze the relationship between public lands and community health and well-being;
3) Foster stewardship: to foster stewardship of public lands and their values and functions; and
4) Inform action: to improve decision-making around the management of public lands for desirable and sustainable outcomes.
